                            <comment id="13485450" author="rohini" created="Sat, 27 Oct 2012 16:12:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Good utility method. Could you also change unit tests to use it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13486451" author="prkommireddi" created="Mon, 29 Oct 2012 22:47:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review Rohini. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding a test case. Also, I have moved the Configuration-&amp;gt;Properties switch into PigContext so stuff other than PigServer can use it too. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13486532" author="rohini" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 00:00:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Prashant,&lt;br/&gt;
   I did not mean that you need to write a unit test for this. It would be overkill &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;. Sorry for not being clear. There are already unit tests which use ConfigurationUtil.toProperties() - TestHBaseStorage.beforeTest() and TestFRJoin.FRJoin.setUpHashTable(). It would be good if you can change those existing tests to use your new API instead of a new test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13486536" author="prkommireddi" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 00:10:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I knew what you meant but wanted to keep my changes isolated. Wasn&apos;t a huge deal to add a 10 line test case. But I will change the above mentioned tests to re-use this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13487044" author="prkommireddi" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 17:38:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rohini, uploading a new test patch. I have also cleaned up some code in TestHBaseStorage and TestFRJoin which had some unused imports and variables. Tests pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13488450" author="rohini" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2012 04:33:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk. Thanks Prashant.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
